abstract: Junior Johnson, the former moonshiner turned hard-charging race car driver who won 50 NASCAR races before becoming a team owner, has died at the age of 88, NASCAR said on Friday.
snippet: Junior Johnson, the former moonshiner turned hard-charging race car driver who won 50 NASCAR races before becoming a team owner, has died at the age of 88, NASCAR said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Junior Johnson, the former moonshiner turned hard-charging race car driver who won 50 NASCAR races before becoming a team owner, has died at the age of 88, NASCAR said on Friday.
headline_main: Nascar Hall-Of-Fame Driver, Team Owner Junior Johnson Dies at 88
headline_print_headline: Nascar Hall-Of-Fame Driver, Team Owner Junior Johnson Dies at 88

abstract: Earlier this week the United States Navy banned the social media app TikTok from government-issued mobile devices, saying the popular short video app represented a "cybersecurity threat."
snippet: Earlier this week the United States Navy banned the social media app TikTok from government-issued mobile devices, saying the popular short video app represented a "cybersecurity threat."
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Earlier this week the United States Navy banned the social media app TikTok from government-issued mobile devices, saying the popular short video app represented a "cybersecurity threat."
headline_main: U.S. Navy Bans TikTok From Government-Issued Mobile Devices
headline_print_headline: U.S. Navy Bans TikTok From Government-Issued Mobile Devices

abstract: Armilla Yanti was returning from her regular Sunday trip to the market in this Indonesian city when a towering tsunami wave crashed ashore. She and her parents survived, but her two sisters were killed on that fateful day on Dec. 26, 2004.Fifteen years on, she frequently relives the traumatic events when recounting her story to visitors at the Aceh Tsunami Museum, where she works as a guide.
snippet: Armilla Yanti was returning from her regular Sunday trip to the market in this Indonesian city when a towering tsunami wave crashed ashore. She and her parents survived, but her two sisters were killed on that fateful day on Dec. 26, 2004.Fifteen ...
lead_paragraph: BANDA ACEH, Indonesia — Armilla Yanti was returning from her regular Sunday trip to the market in this Indonesian city when a towering tsunami wave crashed ashore. She and her parents survived, but her two sisters were killed on that fateful day on Dec. 26, 2004.Fifteen years on, she frequently relives the traumatic events when recounting her story to visitors at the Aceh Tsunami Museum, where she works as a guide.
headline_main: Aceh Tsunami Survivor Hopes Next Generation Will Learn Lessons
headline_print_headline: Aceh Tsunami Survivor Hopes Next Generation Will Learn Lessons

abstract: Boeing Co's stunted Friday debut of its astronaut capsule threatens to dent the U.S. aerospace incumbent's self-declared competitive advantage of mission reliability against the price and innovation strengths of "new space" players like Elon Musk's SpaceX.
snippet: Boeing Co's stunted Friday debut of its astronaut capsule threatens to dent the U.S. aerospace incumbent's self-declared competitive advantage of mission reliability against the price and innovation strengths of "new space" players like Elon Musk'...
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE/CAPE CANAVERAL — Boeing Co's stunted Friday debut of its astronaut capsule threatens to dent the U.S. aerospace incumbent's self-declared competitive advantage of mission reliability against the price and innovation strengths of "new space" players like Elon Musk's SpaceX.
headline_main: Boeing's Failed Starliner Mission Strains 'Reliability' Pitch
headline_print_headline: Boeing's Failed Starliner Mission Strains 'Reliability' Pitch

abstract: Had the language not been removed, administration officials threatened that President Trump would veto must-pass spending legislation, prompting another government shutdown.
snippet: Had the language not been removed, administration officials threatened that President Trump would veto must-pass spending legislation, prompting another government shutdown.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s advisers rejected a bid to force his administration to quickly release military assistance for Ukraine early next year, threatening in recent weeks that he would veto must-pass spending legislation if Congress did not remove the directive.

abstract: He competed on the NASCAR circuit for 12 seasons, became a successful team owner and was one of the first inductees in the organization’s Hall of Fame.
snippet: He competed on the NASCAR circuit for 12 seasons, became a successful team owner and was one of the first inductees in the organization’s Hall of Fame.
lead_paragraph: Junior Johnson, a teenage moonshiner from the North Carolina hills who became one of the greatest drivers in stock-car racing and the personification of its country roots, died on Friday at an assisted living facility in Charlotte, N.C. He was 88.

abstract: Environmentalists and Native Americans can proceed with lawsuits challenging President Donald Trump’s approval of the Keystone XL oil pipeline from Canada, a federal judge in Montana ruled Friday.
snippet: Environmentalists and Native Americans can proceed with lawsuits challenging President Donald Trump’s approval of the Keystone XL oil pipeline from Canada, a federal judge in Montana ruled Friday.
lead_paragraph: BILLINGS, Mont. — Environmentalists and Native Americans can proceed with lawsuits challenging President Donald Trump’s approval of the Keystone XL oil pipeline from Canada, a federal judge in Montana ruled Friday.
headline_main: US Judge Rejects Bid to Kill Keystone Pipeline Lawsuits
headline_print_headline: US Judge Rejects Bid to Kill Keystone Pipeline Lawsuits

abstract: The incident, which was partially caught on video, raised the specter of another anti-Semitic attack. But officials said there was no sign it was a hate crime.
snippet: The incident, which was partially caught on video, raised the specter of another anti-Semitic attack. But officials said there was no sign it was a hate crime.
lead_paragraph: The video, recorded shortly before 4 a.m. Friday, shows a man outside a building lobby. He kicks the bottom pane of a glass entry door violently several times, smashing it but not breaking through.

abstract: An Arizona state trooper shot and killed a Qatari man who was in the U.S. on a student visa after he violently attacked the officer patrolling for drunken drivers along with a member of the group Mothers Against Drunk Driving, authorities said Friday.

lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — An Arizona state trooper shot and killed a Qatari man who was in the U.S. on a student visa after he violently attacked the officer patrolling for drunken drivers along with a member of the group Mothers Against Drunk Driving, authorities said Friday.

abstract: In a darkened arena on the Las Vegas Strip, swimming is being reinvented. Some of the sport's biggest names are competing in the grand finale of the International Swimming League, with flashing lights, pulsating music spun by an on-deck DJ and action-packed racing in a concept the sport has never seen.
